<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-340-758  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 340 758.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  June 12 1989 v23 n24 p47(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Looks, feels like trouble. (Small Talk) (graphical user interfaceintellectual property lawsuits) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Savage, J.A.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The availability of easy-to-use graphical user interfaces isimportant if non-technical users are to be drawn into the market.andO;These interfaces need to maintain a certain similarity so that auser can move from one to another without having to relearneverything.andP;  Therefore, the graphical user interfaces from Apple,Hewlett-Packard, Metaphor, Microsoft and Xerox should maintaincertain features in common.andP;  Unfortunately, Apple and Xerox areboth impeding the progress of the industry and the technology byforcing smaller companies to pay licensing fees or to risk facingthe giants in court.andP;  The lawsuits are getting out of hand and areslowing the progress that could be happening in the industry.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Software PublishersGraphical User InterfaceLegal IssuesCooperationLicensing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>